##-> Allows the firewall host to open chat connections to servers on the 
##-> inside network. It is assumed that the IRC server listens
##-> on the often used default port 6667.
@IPCHAINS@ -A output -i @INTDEV@ -s @INTIP@ 1024:65535 -d @INTNET@ 6667 -p tcp -j ACCEPT
@IPCHAINS@ -A input -i @INTDEV@ -s @INTNET@ 6667 -d @INTIP@ 1024:65535 ! -y -p tcp -j ACCEPT
